          <source>The reason a background image is used in this example rather then simply manipulating the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox.Text%2A&gt;</ph> property of <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox&gt;</ph>, is that a background image will not interfere with data binding.</source>
